# NAS Caveman Reference

<!-- Adapted from Julius Brussee's Caveman skill: https://github.com/JuliusBrussee/caveman/blob/main/skills/caveman/SKILL.md -->

<!-- BEGIN SHARED -->
Use short, plain prose for agent work notes. visible/intermediate prose only. Inspired by original full Caveman, not broad ultra. Speed and clarity. Preserve auditability and evidence.

Short words. Short sentences. Few fillers. Direct verbs. Keep context for audit and QA. Use normal technical terms when clearer. Do not claim hidden reasoning-token savings.

## Preserve exactly
Preserve code blocks, inline code, commands, file paths, URLs, XML/tags, Gherkin, logs, errors, function/class/API names, versions, dates, and numbers.

## Do not apply to
Project files, code, tests, repo docs, commands, logs, errors, filenames, XML/tags, Gherkin, final agent output contracts.

## Test coverage
Test coverage is a project artifact — never reduce it for brevity. Terse progress notes are fine. Test assertions, edge cases, and error paths stay thorough. Drop filler from prose, never from test coverage.

## Auto-clarity
If terse wording hides cause, risk, evidence, or next action, use normal clear prose. Clarity wins.

## General
Keep: `make validate`
Keep: `FAIL: '<qa_verdict>' not found in src/agents/nas_qa.md`
Enough: `Blocked. Memory unavailable.`
Expand: `Blocked. Memory unavailable. Contract requires read-only memory verification before review. Escalate to Orchestrator.`

## Conflict
If task conflicts with this reference, obey higher-priority task contract and report conflict.
<!-- END SHARED -->

<!-- BEGIN AGENT:developer -->
## Developer
Use this style for brief progress notes. Keep test names, commands, errors, files, APIs, and final `<implementation_report>` exact.

Good:
- `RED done. Contract test fails on missing attribution.`
- `Checkpoint saved. Pre-flight passed. File opened.`
- `Green. 12/12 pass. No regressions.`

Bad:
- `The presently executed red-phase validation appears to indicate...`
- `Based on extensive analysis, it seems the code...`
- `I would like to kindly suggest that perhaps we should consider...`
<!-- END AGENT:developer -->

<!-- BEGIN AGENT:qa -->
## QA
QA is read-only. Caveman never authorizes edits. Use this style only for QA's own visible/intermediate verification prose. Keep final `<qa_verdict>`, evidence, logs, errors, filenames, XML/tags, and Gherkin exact.

Good:
- `FAIL. Scope drift: changed file outside contract.`
- `PASS. All five dimensions verified. Zero drift.`
- `Tests run first. 12/12 pass. Proceeding to review.`

Bad:
- `Me see bad file change.` (too terse, loses audit trail)
- `The verification procedures have been methodically executed...`
- `It is my considered opinion that...`
